@flexiarg war-machine/spatial-over-tabular
@title Spatial Over Tabular

! conclusion: A spatial display that shows state as shape and colour earns inhabitation; a tabular display that encodes state as numbers in rows becomes wallpaper.

  + CONTEXT:
    The ant war visualiser is watched at a glance, while markdown tables require deliberate reading and synthesis. The same information becomes obvious when presented spatially and becomes homework when presented only as rows.

  + IF:
    Strategic state needs to be grasped quickly and revisited often rather than read line by line on demand.

  + HOWEVER:
    Tables are still better for precise lookup, and spatial layouts can mislead if they are visually active but semantically arbitrary.

  + THEN:
    Render the same state spatially - active regions glow, neglected regions dim, imbalances show as asymmetric shape - while keeping the table as a precise drill-down fallback.

  + BECAUSE:
    Human vision processes colour, size, position, and motion pre-attentively. Strategic overviews need repeated comprehension at low cost, and spatial layout lowers that cost every time.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Prefer semantically grounded spatial layouts for strategic overviews, then keep exact counts and dates available as tabular drill-down.]
